      <title>Filip and Colleagues Models Floquet-Space Formalism for Coherent Spin System Control</title>
      <link>https://quantumzeitgeist.com/filip-colleagues-models-floquet-space-formalism-coherent-spin-system/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">2026-07-12-filip-and-colleagues-models-floquet-space-formalism-for-cohe</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 12 Jul 2026 15:31:22 GMT</pubDate>
      <category>research</category>
      <description>A Floquet-space formalism is used to model coherent dynamics of a spin system beyond simple rotation, capturing the effects of chiral interactions and showing how Dzyaloshinskii–Moriya interactions tilt spin trajectories. The work reports different behaviors depending on system boundaries and suggests an engineering path for spin-based quantum devices. (via Quantum Zeitgeist)</description>
